snippet.textDisplay:
Most of the song is in hindi and easy to find translations for.. the part the girl sings is in another language - punjabi..  here's the translation for that.. these lines were written by bulleh shah, a very famous sufi poet from the 1800s.. sufism is a whole another topic..

haji lok makke nu jande - people who go on a hajj (pilgrim) go to Mecca, the holy city of muslims in saudi arabia
te asan te jana takht hazare - but i will go to takht hazara, a city in pakistan.. this city was the hometown of ranjha who is the male character from a very famous lover story from the 1600s - heer ranjha.. kinda like romeo and juliet..
te jis wal yaar us wal kaba - which ever side my lover is, that is the direction of kaaba for me.. kaaba is the building at the center of mecca.. the holiest of places for muslims.. all muslims while praying anywhere in the world are supposed to face in the general direction of kaaba..
te asa fol kitaba chare - this one i am not totally sure about.. it literally translates to that i have referred to all four of the books in this regard..

so essentially it means, god loving people go to mecca to see kaaba.. but my lover is my god.. so i will go to his door..

second stanza is slightly unrelated to this one, but by same author - 

itt khadake, dukkad waje, tatta howe chulla  - literally it means, bricks are clashing, a musical instrument is playing, the pan is hot.. basically it means, a resting place is being built, soulful religious music is playing and food is being prepared..
aan fakir te khakha jawan, razi howe bulla - the religious ascetics, who survive on alms, are coming and eating and going.. and bulle shah (the write) is satisfied..

snippet.textDisplay: back again, listening to this for probably the 10th time.  The vocals are so accurate.  Vishal is so incredible with these riffs, and if you notice he constantly changes up the phrasing on the repeat vocals.  Sonu's long tone entrance gives me chills.  This would be a good brass band conversion track.  Parts like 2:05 would be epic with powerful horn parts.  I don't even know what they are saying but I love the music. Listen to the phrasing, precision and range control at 6:02 ... Wow!!
